### 1. Error Handling in Java

Error handling is a vital part of writing robust Java applications. Java uses exceptions to handle errors. Here’s a quick overview of how to handle exceptions effectively:

#### Try-Catch Blocks

Using try-catch blocks allows you to handle exceptions gracefully without crashing the program:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<MyClass> myList = new ArrayList<>();

        try {
            // Attempting to access an index that doesn't exist
            System.out.println(myList.get(0));
        } catch (IndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
            System.out.println("Caught an exception: " + e.getMessage());
        }

        // Adding an element to the list
        myList.add(new MyClass("Banana"));
    }
}
```

### 2. More Complex Data Structures

