### 1. Data Persistence

You can use serialization to save and load the `EnergyDemandModel` object to a file. Here’s a simple implementation:

```java
import java.io.*;

class EnergyDemandModel implements Serializable {
    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;
    private Map<String, EnergySector> sectors;

    public EnergyDemandModel() {
        this.sectors = new HashMap<>();
    }

    public void addSector(EnergySector sector) {
        sectors.put(sector.getName(), sector);
    }

    public EnergySector getSector(String name) {
        return sectors.get(name);
    }

    public void saveToFile(String filename) throws IOException {
        try (ObjectOutputStream oos = new ObjectOutputStream(new FileOutputStream(filename))) {
            oos.writeObject(this);
        }
    }

    public static EnergyDemandModel loadFromFile(String filename) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {
        try (ObjectInputStream ois = new ObjectInputStream(new FileInputStream(filename))) {
            return (EnergyDemandModel) ois.readObject();
        }
    }
}
```

### 2. Calculating Total Demand

You can add a method to calculate the total demand across all sectors:

```java
public double getTotalDemand() {
    double total = 0;
    for (EnergySector sector : sectors.values()) {
        for (double demandValue : sector.getDemand().values()) {
            total += demandValue;
        }
    }
    return total;
}
```

### 3. User Interaction

You can use a simple console-based interface to interact with the user. Here’s an example:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        EnergyDemandModel model = new EnergyDemandModel();
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        String command;

        do {
            System.out.println("Enter command (add, total, save, load, exit): ");
            command = scanner.nextLine().toLowerCase();

            switch (command) {
                case "add":
                    System.out.println("Enter energy type (Solar, Wind, Gas): ");
                    String type = scanner.nextLine();
                    EnergySector sector = EnergySectorFactory.createEnergySector(type);
                    System.out.println("Enter region: ");
                    String region = scanner.nextLine();
                    System.out.println("Enter demand (MW): ");
                    double demandValue = scanner.nextDouble();
                    scanner.nextLine(); // Consume newline
                    sector.setDemand(region, demandValue);
                    model.addSector(sector);
                    break;

                case "total":
                    System.out.println("Total demand across all sectors: " + model.getTotalDemand() + " MW");
                    break;

                case "save":
                    try {
                        model.saveToFile("energyDemandModel.dat");
                        System.out.println("Model saved.");
                    } catch (IOException e) {
                        System.err.println("Error saving model: " + e.getMessage());
                    }
                    break;

                case "load":
                    try {
                        model = EnergyDemandModel.loadFromFile("energyDemandModel.dat");
                        System.out.println("Model loaded.");
                    } catch (IOException | ClassNotFoundException e) {
                        System.err.println("Error loading model: " + e.getMessage());
                    }
                    break;

                case "exit":
                    System.out.println("Exiting...");
                    break;

                default:
                    System.out.println("Unknown command.");
            }
        } while (!command.equals("exit"));

        scanner.close();
    }
}
```

